      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: A = 10kx6 + 15kx6 = 150k\n        B = 15kx12 = 180k\nStep 2: Ratio = 150:180 = 5:6\nStep 3: A=3500x5/11=1591, B=1909\n\n  Month: 1────6──────────12\n  A:     |=10k=|===15k====|\n  B:     |======15k=======|\n\nTRICK:\nSplit periods at capital change\nEffective = sum(Capital x Time)\nRatio 5:6 → 1 part = 3500/11\n\nAnswer: A = Rs 1591, B = Rs 1909 ✓",
